37
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:40,740
The chairman is amazing!

38
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:45,800
Wow, it happened last night, and our students are already on it. Huh?

39
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:48,190
- This is all your fault. 
 - Come on.

40
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:51,470
I invited the chairman to staff dinner purely to flirt with him.

41
00:02:51,470 --> 00:02:53,450
Who dared pour cold water on my fragile heart,

42
00:02:53,450 --> 00:02:56,270
saying she'll date when the flowers bloom?

43
00:02:56,270 --> 00:02:57,790
Flowers, my foot.

44
00:02:57,790 --> 00:03:00,780
I'm absolutely sure it won't bloom.

45
00:03:01,170 --> 00:03:06,220
♫  Now, I look at you  ♫

46
00:03:06,220 --> 00:03:11,380
♫  Now, you save me  ♫

47
00:03:11,380 --> 00:03:18,520
♫  Let go of the hatred  ♫

48
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:22,730
♫  Embrace me  ♫

49
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:28,500
My endgame is him shamefully stepping down from the chairman seat.

50
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:31,200
   
 Hey. 

51
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:33,610
 You must have the inauguration ceremony. 

52
00:03:33,610 --> 00:03:36,700
Make it big and fancy. I'll invite the whole town.

53
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:40,120
 To completely crush Yoon Jae Ho's spirit! 

54
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,010
 Hey. 

55
00:03:41,010 --> 00:03:42,870
Are you listening? Hey, hey!

56
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:44,310
Are you listening to me?

57
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:46,120
Father, I...

58
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,530
Anyway, get the Administrative Director on the line.

59
00:03:48,530 --> 00:03:50,750
 He's there, right? I know he is. 

60
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:52,830
 Put him on. 

61
00:03:52,830 --> 00:03:55,310
Yes, I'm on now, CEO.

62
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:59,290
Yes, I understand. Yes.

63
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:07,720
All you have to do is attend.

64
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:10,760
We'll prepare everything, Chairman.

65
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:13,150
Make it as small as possible.

66
00:04:13,150 --> 00:04:16,990
As if we're barely doing it.

67
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:25,180
I'll do my best.

68
00:04:33,260 --> 00:04:35,890
Miss Yoon, headed to class? The field?

69
00:04:35,890 --> 00:04:37,970
Yes, I'm headed out.

70
00:04:37,970 --> 00:04:39,500
Since it's the fourth-period,

71
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,950
should the Creative Experience Department have lunch together afterward?

72
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:44,530
- We have things to discuss. 
 - Pardon?

73
00:04:44,530 --> 00:04:46,390
If you're on your way to the field,

74
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,670
drop by the school health office

75
00:04:47,670 --> 00:04:50,490
and tell Mr. Hong to come to the cafeteria at lunchtime.

76
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:51,590
He's not picking up.

77
00:04:51,590 --> 00:04:56,190
Sir, did you take something on again?

78
00:04:56,970 --> 00:04:59,950
Everyone's busy. As if we have time to kill.

79
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:03,470
But I'm the youngest department head, so I have no choice.

80
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:05,640
What is it this time?

81
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:07,450
   

82
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:13,020
I am not awkward.

83
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:15,280
I'm totally fine.

84
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:24,640
Miss Yoon, you're here.

85
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,740
Yes, I'm here.

86
00:05:27,740 --> 00:05:29,640
Mr. Lee Jae Gyu wanted

87
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:33,750
the Creative Experience Department to have lunch together.

88
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:38,620
Apparently, we took on the chairman's inauguration ceremony or whatever.

89
00:05:38,620 --> 00:05:40,880
Oh, I see.

90
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:44,200
What's with these inauguration ceremonies?

91
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:47,080
Only the teachers get to suffer, right?

92
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:49,980
Should we pull that crazy lilac out of the ground?

93
00:05:49,980 --> 00:05:52,680
That's cheating.

94
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,390
What? No warning at all?

95
00:05:54,390 --> 00:05:56,100
With the door wide open,

96
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:59,090
I could hear everything and had no chance to give a warning.

97
00:05:59,090 --> 00:06:01,400
"Chairman or whatever"?

98
00:06:01,830 --> 00:06:03,680
Sounds like you have grievances about my inauguration ceremony.

99
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,980
It's just that I'm worried.

100
00:06:05,980 --> 00:06:07,950
- Worried about me? 
 - You know how it is.

101
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:10,470
You'll make a fool out of yourself

102
00:06:10,470 --> 00:06:13,730
when you have to quit shortly after the inauguration ceremony.

103
00:06:13,730 --> 00:06:17,940
I see! You're still thinking about our bet.

104
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:19,560
I had forgotten about it.

105
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:23,430
- What? 
 - Let's accept the results once we have it.

106
00:06:23,430 --> 00:06:26,500
Don't worry about whether the flower will bloom or not.

107
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:30,400
Don't spend days thinking about it and don't lose sleep over it.

108
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:33,200
I guess you find the stakes too trivial for the bet.

109
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:36,690
But I bet something I despise more than death itself.

110
00:06:36,690 --> 00:06:40,230
So, it's hard for me to be cool like you, Chairman.

111
00:06:40,740 --> 00:06:42,790
That's none of my business.

112
00:06:42,790 --> 00:06:45,090
Let's not touch the tree.

113
00:06:45,090 --> 00:06:48,580
That would be cowardly and petty.

114
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:57,130
Mr. Hong, I'll get going.

115
00:06:57,130 --> 00:06:59,570
Yes, see you later.

116
00:07:35,710 --> 00:07:37,370
Yes?

117
00:07:51,460 --> 00:07:54,850
Guys, the bell rang. Hurry up and gather.

118
00:08:01,930 --> 00:08:05,310
Today, we'll be learning volleyball.

119
00:08:11,090 --> 00:08:14,250
- Mr. Gong? 
 - Today, we'll learn how to serve.

120
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:16,430
- What are we learning today? 
 - How to serve!

121
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:18,770
Types of serves...

122
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:26,730
Okay. So, who wants to lead the inauguration ceremony?

123
00:08:26,730 --> 00:08:30,490
Miss Yoon is so good at events like this.

124
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:34,110
She got good at it because you always make Miss Yoon do it.

125
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:36,400
You didn't have to go there.

126
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,500
I'll take this one.

127
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:40,260
I'll do it with her.

128
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:43,300
You're our only nurse, so you need to stay in the school health office.

129
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:45,090
You can't lead events like this.

130
00:08:45,090 --> 00:08:47,410
- But... 
 - I can do it by myself.

131
00:08:47,410 --> 00:08:51,610
Mr. Jang Seung Jo said not to make Miss Su Ah take on more work

132
00:08:51,610 --> 00:08:55,680
because you're preparing for the math competition with Miss Cha Ji Hye starting this week.

133
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:59,830
He has been acting all high and mighty ever since he became the Math Department head.

134
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:06,340
What? So, you'd already decided it would be me.

135
00:09:06,340 --> 00:09:09,200
I don't want to do it, either. I'm busy, too.

136
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:12,610
I know. Of course, you're busy since the semester just started.

137
00:09:12,610 --> 00:09:16,520
I know it'll be tough to prepare for the inauguration ceremony on top of everything.

138
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:18,800
I know, but...

139
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:21,600
Fine!

140
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,910
This is too much.

141
00:09:22,910 --> 00:09:25,190
Let me speak to the vice principal again.

142
00:09:25,190 --> 00:09:26,820
Miss Yoon, don't do it.

143
00:09:26,820 --> 00:09:28,770
Don't do it, okay?

144
00:09:33,210 --> 00:09:37,070
What a surprise. I thought he'd push.

145
00:09:37,070 --> 00:09:39,970
The stocks must be doing well today.

146
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:47,910
Miss.

147
00:09:47,910 --> 00:09:49,730
I'll do it.

148
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:55,870
Our gym is so old that it always leaks during rain.

149
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:58,800
And it's like this with a brief shower in the middle of the night.

150
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,820
So, try not to put things in this area if possible. Got it?

151
00:10:01,820 --> 00:10:03,360
Got it.

152
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:13,240
You can make fun of me. Or ask me questions.

153
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:17,030
- Pardon? 
 - The teachers, the students, ladies, the security guards...

154
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:18,720
They all came by and said their piece.

155
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:22,450
Feel free to ask about anything you're curious about, Mr. Gong.

156
00:10:22,450 --> 00:10:24,720
The bet from last night?

157
00:10:26,340 --> 00:10:28,120
In that case...

158
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:31,390
I do have something I'm curious about.

159
00:10:31,390 --> 00:10:32,970
May I ask you?

160
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:37,430
Shoot. What's the difference between 100 people and 101 asking me?

161
00:10:46,090 --> 00:10:47,800
What?

162
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:58,860
Want to go off-campus for tonkatsu with me during lunch tomorrow?

163
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:01,520
- What do you think? 
 - Even if it's on me?

164
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,900
The school lunch is so bad.

165
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:05,020
I asked, what do you think?

166
00:11:09,650 --> 00:11:11,210
Where are you going, Miss Yoon?

167
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:13,450
To fix the goalpost.

168
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:21,300
Father,

169
00:11:21,300 --> 00:11:24,310
you've let this car sit for too long.

170
00:11:24,310 --> 00:11:26,000
Right?

171
00:11:26,970 --> 00:11:30,480
I keep getting more and more scared.

172
00:11:31,180 --> 00:11:35,180
After Ji Won's parents went like that,

173
00:11:35,180 --> 00:11:37,540
I white-knuckled my way through it.

174
00:11:37,540 --> 00:11:41,900
But since last year, I feel nauseous and my vision gets blurry

175
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:44,430
when I sit in the driver's seat.

176
00:11:44,430 --> 00:11:47,660
I'm thinking of getting rid of it.

177
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:52,090
Still, you never know when you might need it.

178
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:20,960
It's running fine.

179
00:12:21,910 --> 00:12:26,070
My Ho Seok has always been good with cars.

180
00:12:26,070 --> 00:12:28,040
But while serving as Head of Finance,

181
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:31,600
when did you have time to learn about fixing cars?

182
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:35,040
A smart kid sure is different.

183
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,800
It's because Ho Seok taught me well.

184
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:41,700
Thank you. I better clean the car for the first time in a while.

185
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:45,570
- I'll get going. 
 - Okay, thank you.

186
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:49,580
- Okay, see you. 
 - Yes.

187
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:00,560
   

188
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:03,890
   

189
00:13:13,530 --> 00:13:15,380
 Over here! 

190
00:13:20,030 --> 00:13:23,530
Why would a teacher handle all that?

191
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,940
Yes.

192
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,970
Do you have a moment?

193
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:43,550
We never see each other, although we work at the same school.

194
00:13:43,550 --> 00:13:46,100
Unless I come looking for you.

195
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:48,970
Sorry. I was busy with company matters.

196
00:13:48,970 --> 00:13:53,530
Is that why you said no when I asked you out to dinner?

197
00:13:53,870 --> 00:13:55,270
Sorry.

198
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:57,410
So, what do you want to say?

199
00:13:57,890 --> 00:14:00,600
I'm not sure if this is the right place for it.

200
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,740
Just say it. It's okay.

201
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:09,700
Why did you make such a bet with Yoon Ji Won again?

202
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:14,980
Why do I need to explain that to you?

203
00:14:18,870 --> 00:14:23,650
After you transferred out of our high school

204
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:26,150
and started college,

205
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:30,520
you remember how I tracked you down. Right?

206
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:36,520
Even after that, I called you on special occasions

207
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,980
and even went to your graduation.

208
00:14:40,390 --> 00:14:43,330
I went to the airport when you left for Dubai.

209
00:14:43,330 --> 00:14:45,330
You did.

210
00:14:45,780 --> 00:14:47,510
Even though I told you many times not to.

211
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:50,670
Why do you think I stuck around even when you pushed me away?

212
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:54,560
It's because...

213
00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:59,950
I like you.

214
00:15:01,820 --> 00:15:05,550
Ever since we were in the same class in high school,

215
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:07,720
I've liked you.

216
00:15:10,170 --> 00:15:12,340
Until now.

217
00:15:12,340 --> 00:15:14,310
Without wavering.

218
00:15:14,860 --> 00:15:17,620
- Ji Hye. 
 - What if the flowers do bloom?

219
00:15:17,620 --> 00:15:20,540
Will you really date her like back in the day?

220
00:15:21,510 --> 00:15:23,770
Back in the day?

221
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:30,990
I know everything.

222
00:15:31,990 --> 00:15:35,750
Yoon Ji Won and I had no secrets back then.

223
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:44,280
So, I know this bet is meaningless to you and Yoon Ji Won now.

224
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:48,520
- But.. 
 - Yoon Ji Won told you about that?

225
00:15:49,050 --> 00:15:50,040
Yes.

226
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:53,000
How did Yoon Ji Won describe our relationship?

227
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:56,450
She said you secretly dated without telling anyone.

228
00:15:56,450 --> 00:15:58,550
Barely three months.

229
00:15:58,550 --> 00:16:02,930
And it ended when you left abruptly.

230
00:16:05,030 --> 00:16:07,740
Barely three months...

231
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:10,280
And it ended...

232
00:16:12,270 --> 00:16:14,350
Is that really what she said?

233
00:16:14,350 --> 00:16:15,860
Why?

234
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:18,400
You need something more?

235
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:26,910
Gosh.

236
00:16:37,780 --> 00:16:40,050
Geez! You scared me.

237
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:41,650
What's with you?

238
00:16:41,650 --> 00:16:42,710
You.

239
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:44,210
You?

240
00:16:44,210 --> 00:16:47,020
Yes, you. Yoon Ji Won.

241
00:16:47,740 --> 00:16:49,660
Excuse me.

242
00:16:50,370 --> 00:16:54,440
 How come Miss Yoon Ji Won is that way? 

243
00:16:57,800 --> 00:17:00,810
 I'm not talking behind her back. 

244
00:17:00,810 --> 00:17:03,620
 She needs to know to separate work and life. 

245
00:17:03,620 --> 00:17:06,340
 I understand there's family drama, but... 

246
00:17:06,340 --> 00:17:08,270
 She only thinks... 

247
00:17:08,270 --> 00:17:10,960
Don't you think this is weirder?

248
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,120
I know, but...

249
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:16,520
 It's inappropriate to get wishy-washy by getting personal feelings involved. 

250
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:21,120
 Back in my day, I did anything and everything the higher-ups told me to do. 

251
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:24,030
Vice Principal, you're right. But still...

252
00:17:24,030 --> 00:17:27,560
it's not like Miss Yoon has free time.

253
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:28,970
She has a lot on her plate.

254
00:17:28,970 --> 00:17:30,770
Gosh, come on.

255
00:17:30,770 --> 00:17:34,480
How much work could a B-level curriculum possibly be?

256
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:38,440
 Vice Principal, please don't say that. 

257
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,810
 You like Miss Yoon. 

258
00:17:40,810 --> 00:17:43,300
 You know there's a lot to do in P.E. 

259
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:46,970
- Come on! 
  - I like her when she shuts up and works obediently. 

260
00:17:46,970 --> 00:17:51,590
Anyway, I'll discuss this with the Head of Academic Affairs.

261
00:17:51,590 --> 00:17:53,700
So you don't have to worry, Vice Principal.

262
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:58,060
Me? This is not for me or the chairman.

263
00:17:58,060 --> 00:18:00,890
This is to satisfy our CEO.

264
00:18:00,890 --> 00:18:05,820
Let's make it as big, fancy, and grand as he wants.

